				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Summer Storm: Regimental Wargame Scenarios for the Battle of Gettysburg" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>The Battle of Gettysburg was one of the turning points of the American Civil War. Refight the battle on the game table and see if you can change the course of history!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These scenarios are designed to be used with almost any American Civil War regimental or brigade level set of rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules are included for figures based on 20, 30, 40, 50, and 100 historic men per figure/stand.  &amp;#10;Times are given for 10, 15, and 20 minutes per game turn.  &amp;#10;Maps are in full color, as are the numerous color photographs of the modern battlefield.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scenarios include:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     McPherson Ridge&amp;#10;     Heth Renews the Attack              &amp;#10;     Blocher&amp;rsquo;s Knoll&amp;#10;     Longstreet&amp;rsquo;s Assault (Round Top to the Peach Orchard)&amp;#10;     Little Round Top&amp;#10;     The Peach Orchard&amp;#10;     Cemetery Ridge              &amp;#10;     East Cemetery Hill&amp;#10;     Night at Cemetery Hill (Extended scenario with Rodes&amp;rsquo; Division)&amp;#10;     Opportunity at Culp&amp;rsquo;s Hill&amp;#10;     Culp&amp;rsquo;s Hill at Dawn&amp;#10;     South Cavalry Field&amp;#10;     And a full order of battle!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
